            <div class='post' itemprop='text'>
              <p>As a thought, generally (!) when people are installing using Docker they‚Äôre using the (Ubuntu based) setup script:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<a href="https://github.com/getredash/setup/blob/master/setup.sh" class="inline-onebox" rel="noopener nofollow ugc">setup/setup.sh at master ¬∑ getredash/setup ¬∑ GitHub</a> ‚Üê original, very out of date</li>
<li>
<a href="https://github.com/getnewdash/setup/blob/master/setup.sh" class="inline-onebox" rel="noopener nofollow ugc">setup/setup.sh at master ¬∑ getnewdash/setup ¬∑ GitHub</a> ‚Üê newer, kept up to date</li>
</ul>
<p>When using that script, it creates an <code>/opt/redash</code> directory on the <em>host</em> (not inside the docker container), with an <code>env</code> file inside that directory containing the settings/values.</p>
<p>So, the references to <code>/opt/redash/env</code> that you‚Äôve seen are most likely talking about the <code>env</code> file from that scripted setup.</p>
            </div>

